  "text": "Kafka Consumer Offset Commit Flow - From Consumer to __consumer_offsets Topic\n\n## Overview\nThe consumer offset commit flow is a complex multi-step process that involves both the client-side consumer and the broker-side group coordinator. This flow ensures that consumer offsets are persisted and can be recovered on rebalance or restart.\n\n## Client-Side Flow\n\n### 1. KafkaConsumer.commitSync()\nEntry point at `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer.java:1039-1041`. The public API delegates to the delegate (ClassicKafkaConsumer).\n\n### 2. ClassicKafkaConsumer.commitSync()\nImplementation at `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ClassicKafkaConsumer.java:736-750`. This method:\n- Calls `coordinator.commitOffsetsSync()` with the offsets and a timer\n- Throws TimeoutException if the commit doesn't complete within the timeout\n\n### 3. ConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync()\nCore synchronous commit logic at `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java:1140-1176`. This method:\n- Invokes pending offset commit callbacks\n- Calls `sendOffsetCommitRequest()` to send the actual request to the coordinator\n- Polls the client until the response is received or timeout occurs\n- Throws CommitFailedException or RebalanceInProgressException on unrecoverable errors\n\n### 4. ConsumerCoordinator.sendOffsetCommitRequest()\nImplementation at `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java:1270-1343`. This method:\n- Constructs an OffsetCommitRequest containing the offsets to commit\n- Includes groupId, memberId, generation ID, and the TopicPartition->OffsetAndMetadata mappings\n- Sends the request to the group coordinator broker via `client.send()`\n- Registers an OffsetCommitResponseHandler to process the response\n\n## Broker-Side Flow\n\n### 5. KafkaApis.handleOffsetCommitRequest()\nBroker request handler at `core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala:272-365`. This method:\n- Receives the OffsetCommitRequest from the network\n- Performs authorization checks (verifies read access to the group)\n- Filters topics by authorization (TOPIC resource)\n- Resolves topic IDs to names if needed\n- Delegates to `groupCoordinator.commitOffsets()` for the actual offset commit\n\n### 6. GroupCoordinatorService.commitOffsets()\nCoordinator service entry point at `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java:1971-2002`. This method:\n- Validates that the coordinator is active\n- Calls `runtime.scheduleWriteOperation()` to schedule a write operation on the coordinator\n- The operation will be executed by a coordinator shard, which will process the commit and write to the log\n- Returns a CompletableFuture that completes when the write is done\n\n### 7. GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset()\nShard-level handler at `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java:852-857`. This is a simple delegation method that calls:\n- `offsetMetadataManager.commitOffset()` with the request context and offset commit request data\n\n### 8. OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset()\nCore offset commit logic at `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java:600-665`. This method:\n- Validates the offset commit request (checks authorization, metadata size)\n- For classic groups, reschedules member heartbeats if the group is in STABLE or PREPARING_REBALANCE state\n- Creates an OffsetCommitResponseData for the response\n- For each topic and partition in the request, creates a CoordinatorRecord using `GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord()`\n- Returns a CoordinatorResult containing the records to be written and the response data\n\n### 9. GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord()\nRecord creation at `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.java:467-491`. This method:\n- Creates an OffsetCommitKey with the groupId, topic, and partition\n- Creates an OffsetCommitValue containing:\n  - The committed offset\n  - Leader epoch\n  - Metadata\n  - Commit timestamp\n  - Expiration timestamp (for TTL-based retention)\n  - Topic ID\n- Wraps these in a CoordinatorRecord with the appropriate version\n\n## Log Append\n\nThe CoordinatorRecord objects created above are then appended to the __consumer_offsets topic by the coordinator runtime. The actual log append is handled by:\n- `CoordinatorRuntime.scheduleWriteOperation()` which manages the write to the underlying Kafka log\n- The records are written to the __consumer_offsets topic partition that corresponds to the group's partition (calculated via hash of groupId)\n- The operation ensures all in-sync replicas acknowledge the write before returning success to the client\n\n## Summary\n\nThe flow creates a chain of responsibility from the consumer application to the persistent __consumer_offsets topic:\n1. Consumer calls commitSync() on KafkaConsumer\n2. Request is routed through ClassicKafkaConsumer -> ConsumerCoordinator\n3. OffsetCommitRequest is sent to the group coordinator broker\n4. Broker validates and routes through KafkaApis -> GroupCoordinatorService\n5. Coordinator shard processes via OffsetMetadataManager\n6. Offset commit records are created and appended to __consumer_offsets log\n7. Response is sent back to client confirming persistence across replicas"
